到.definition: to reach; to arrive; to leave for; to go to; to (a place); until (a time); up to (a point); (verb complement indicating arriving at a place or reaching a point); considerate; thoughtful; thorough

到了.definition: at last; finally; in the end

到什麼山上，唱什麼歌.pinyin: dao4 shen2 me5 shan1 shang4 , chang4 shen2 me5 ge1
到什麼山上，唱什麼歌.definition: lit. whatever mountain one is on, one should sing its songs (idiom); fig. when in Rome, do as the Romans do

到任.definition: to take office; to assume a post

到位.definition: to get to the intended location; to be in place; to be in position; precise; well (done)

到場.definition: to show up; present (at the scene)

到家.definition: perfect; excellent; brought to the utmost degree

到底.definition: finally; in the end; when all is said and done; after all; to the end; to the last

到得.definition: to arrive at (some place or time)

到手.definition: to take possession of; to get hold of

到手軟.definition: (do a manual task) until one's hands go limp with exhaustion

到時候.definition: when the moment comes; at that time

到期.definition: to fall due (loan etc); to expire (visa etc); to mature (investment bond etc)

到期日.definition: due date; expiry date; maturity date

到案.definition: to make an appearance in court

到此為止.definition: to stop at this point; to end here; to call it a day

到賬.definition: (of money) to arrive in an account

到頭.definition: to the end (of); at the end of; in the end; to come to an end

到頭來.definition: in the end; finally; as a result

到點.definition: it's time (to do sth); the time has come
